BEGIN:VEVENT
DESCRIPTION:Dear Team\,  Apex runs in the cloud and that makes cloud educat
 ion a key part of engineering and product skill sets therefore we're launc
 hing a monthly  Lunch & Learn Series<https://apexclearing.atlassian.net/wi
 ki/spaces/ADC/pages/8231485531/Cloud+Platform+Lunch+Learn+Series>\, design
 ed to foster continuous learning\, cross-functional collaboration\, and al
 ignment across our organization. With industries rapidly evolving—especi
 ally in the technology and cloud domains—staying informed and adaptable 
 is essential for success.\n\n\n\nOur focus will be on the Ascend Cloud Nat
 ive Platform and Google Cloud technologies\, showcasing their benefits\, r
 eal-world applications\, and alignment to our company-wide goals. These in
 teractive sessions will cater to all skill levels\, promoting knowledge sh
 aring while fostering engagement and adoption of these critical tools.\n\n
 \n\nKey Objectives of the Series:\n\n  *   Foster Cross-Team Collaboration
 : Break silos between technical\, non-technical\, and executive teams whil
 e aligning on tools like Ascend and Google Cloud.\n  *   Provide Accessibl
 e Learning: Tailored content for varying roles ensures simplified educatio
 n\, relevant to each team’s responsibilities.\n  *   Boost Adoption & Dr
 ive Efficiency: Real-world demos and case studies will help teams unlock t
 he full potential of our platforms.\n  *   Align Business & Technology Goa
 ls: Learn how technology drives innovation\, scalability\, and strategic o
 bjectives at every level.\n  *   Encourage Continuous Learning & Engagemen
 t: The relaxed format motivates participation and professional growth whil
 e fostering collaboration.\n\n\n\nSession Structure:\n\n  *   Introduction
  (5 Min): Overview of the topic and session takeaways.\n  *   Deep Dive in
 to the Topic (25 Min):\n     *   Target Audience segments\n        *   Exe
 cutives: Strategic overviews\, ROI insights\, and business impact.\n      
   *   Non-Technical Teams: Simplified applications for day-to-day use.\n  
       *   Technical Teams: Technical workflows\, insights\, and best pract
 ices.\n  *   Hands-On Demo/Interactive Activity (15 Min): Live demonstrati
 ons to connect theory to practice.\n     *   *We will try to include a dem
 o/hands-on as much as we can but not guaranteed for all sessions.\n  *   Q
 &A and Closing Next Steps (5 Min): Open floor for questions and sharing fu
 rther resources.\n\n\n\nDetails of the Second Session:\n\n  *   Topic: Unl
 ocking API Excellence: Harnessing Apigee for Modernization\, Governance\, 
 and Innovation\n  *   Date: Last Wednesday of every month. Based on who is
  presenting the topic the time/time zone varies (if its Belfast/Manila it 
 will be their lunch time) and the content will be shared offline via below
  confluence location.\n  *   Time: 7 AM – 8 AM PST (since the presenters
  are in Belfast time zone)\n  *   Mode: Virtual (via Zoom)\n  *   Audience
 : Open to all interested (Slides and recordings will also be shared post-s
 ession)\n  *   Topics: Added in confluence<https://apexclearing.atlassian.
 net/wiki/spaces/ADC/pages/8250622042/Lunch+Learn+Series+Topic+Roster>\n\n\
 n\nWe look forward to your participation. Let’s align our expertise and 
 drive innovation together! Please feel free to forward a needed!\n\n\n\n**
 This is not targeted for an office or a time or specific audience. We don'
 t expect everyone to join live also. Goal is to record and post the slides
  + video on confluence so that it will become an inventory and can be acce
 ssed by anyone any time\n\n\n\nVineeth Ayyat Kochaniyan\nSr Director\, Pro
 duct Management\nvayyatkochaniyan@apexfintexhsolutions.com<mailto:vayyatko
 chaniyan@apexfintexhsolutions.com>\n\n\nVineeth Ayyat Kochaniyan is inviti
 ng you to a scheduled Zoom meeting.\n\nJoin Zoom Meeting - - Please note h
 osts must use Zoom app or link to start this meeting.\nhttps://apexclearin
 g.zoom.us/j/97797610700?from=addon\n\nOne tap mobile\n+12532050468\,\,9779
 7610700# US\n+12532158782\,\,97797610700# US (Tacoma)\n\nDial by your loca
 tion\n+1 253 205 0468 US\n+1 253 215 8782 US (Tacoma)\n+1 346 248 7799 US 
 (Houston)\n+1 669 444 9171 US\n+1 669 900 6833 US (San Jose)\n+1 719 359 4
 580 US\n+1 309 205 3325 US\n+1 312 626 6799 US (Chicago)\n+1 360 209 5623 
 US\n+1 386 347 5053 US\n+1 507 473 4847 US\n+1 564 217 2000 US\n+1 646 876
  9923 US (New York)\n+1 646 931 3860 US\n+1 689 278 1000 US\n+1 301 715 85
 92 US (Washington DC)\n+1 305 224 1968 US\nMeeting ID: 977 9761 0700\nFind
  your local number: https://apexclearing.zoom.us/u/abtNprCVHr\n\nJoin by S
 IP\n97797610700@zoomcrc.com\n\nJoin by H.323\n144.195.19.161 (US West)\n20
 6.247.11.121 (US East)\n115.114.131.7 (India Mumbai)\n115.114.115.7 (India
  Hyderabad)\n159.124.15.191 (Amsterdam Netherlands)\n159.124.47.249 (Germa
 ny)\n159.124.104.213 (Australia Sydney)\n159.124.74.212 (Australia Melbour
 ne)\n170.114.180.219 (Singapore)\n64.211.144.160 (Brazil)\n159.124.132.243
  (Mexico)\n159.124.168.213 (Canada Toronto)\n159.124.196.25 (Canada Vancou
