BEGIN:VEVENT
DESCRIPTION:SOAR Training\n\nSecurity analysts currently face a significant
  bottleneck in their investigation workflow\, spending the majority of the
 ir time manually navigating between different systems and executing variou
 s commands to gather case details and enrichment data. This manual process
  is both time-consuming and prone to inconsistencies.\nSolution\nCase View
  transforms this experience by providing a centralized\, customizable dash
 board that consolidates all relevant case information in a single interfac
 e. Through our SOAR (Security Orchestration\, Automation\, and Response) p
 latform\, analysts can now leverage pre-configured widgets and tabs that a
 utomatically populate with data from previously executed actions and enric
 hment processes.\nThis streamlined approach eliminates the need for repeti
 tive manual tasks\, allowing analysts to focus on high-value analysis and 
 decision-making rather than data collection and navigation.\nhttps://cloud
 .google.com/chronicle/docs/soar/investigate/working-with-alerts/define-def
 ault-alert-view-admin\n Konrad Uminski is inviting you to a scheduled Zoom
  meeting.\n\nJoin Zoom Meeting - - Please note hosts must use Zoom app or 
 link to start this meeting.\nhttps://apexclearing.zoom.us/j/97738145357?fr
 om=addon\n\nOne tap mobile\n+13126266799\,\,97738145357# US (Chicago)\n+13
 092053325\,\,97738145357# US\n\nDial by your location\n+1 312 626 6799 US 
 (Chicago)\n+1 309 205 3325 US\n+1 646 931 3860 US\n+1 301 715 8592 US (Was
 hington DC)\n+1 305 224 1968 US\n+1 646 876 9923 US (New York)\n+1 507 473
