BEGIN:VEVENT
DESCRIPTION:Dear Team\,  Apex runs in the cloud and that makes cloud educat
 ion a key part of engineering and product skill sets therefore we're launc
 hing a monthly Lunch & Learn Series<https://apexclearing.atlassian.net/wik
 i/spaces/ADC/pages/8231485531/Cloud+Platform+Lunch+Learn+Series>\, designe
 d to foster continuous learning\, cross-functional collaboration\, and ali
 gnment across our organization. With industries rapidly evolving—especia
 lly in the technology and cloud domains—staying informed and adaptable i
 s essential for success.\n\n\n\nOur focus will be on the Ascend Cloud Nati
 ve Platform and Google Cloud technologies\, showcasing their benefits\, re
 al-world applications\, and alignment to our company-wide goals. These int
 eractive sessions will cater to all skill levels\, promoting knowledge sha
 ring while fostering engagement and adoption of these critical tools.\n\n\
 n\nKey Objectives of the Series:\n\n  *   Foster Cross-Team Collaboration:
  Break silos between technical\, non-technical\, and executive teams while
  aligning on tools like Ascend and Google Cloud.\n  *   Provide Accessible
  Learning: Tailored content for varying roles ensures simplified education
 \, relevant to each team’s responsibilities.\n  *   Boost Adoption & Dri
 ve Efficiency: Real-world demos and case studies will help teams unlock th
 e full potential of our platforms.\n  *   Align Business & Technology Goal
 s: Learn how technology drives innovation\, scalability\, and strategic ob
 jectives at every level.\n  *   Encourage Continuous Learning & Engagement
 : The relaxed format motivates participation and professional growth while
  fostering collaboration.\n\n\nSession Structure:\n\n  *   Introduction (5
  Min): Overview of the topic and session takeaways.\n  *   Deep Dive into 
 the Topic (25 Min):\n     *   Target Audience segments\n        *   Execut
 ives: Strategic overviews\, ROI insights\, and business impact.\n        *
    Non-Technical Teams: Simplified applications for day-to-day use.\n     
    *   Technical Teams: Technical workflows\, insights\, and best practice
 s.\n  *   Hands-On Demo/Interactive Activity (15 Min): Live demonstrations
  to connect theory to practice.\n     *   *We will try to include a demo/h
 ands-on as much as we can but not guaranteed for all sessions.\n  *   Q&A 
 and Closing Next Steps (5 Min): Open floor for questions and sharing furth
 er resources.\n\n\n\nDetails of the Sixth Session:\n\n  *\nTopic: Apex FTE
  - Trading Technology Infrastructure\n  *   Date: Last Wednesday of every 
 month. Based on who is presenting the topic the time/time zone varies (if 
 its Belfast/Manila it will be their lunch time) and the content will be sh
 ared offline via below confluence location.\n  *   Time: 12 PM – 1:00 PM
  CST (since the presenters are in CST time zone)\n  *   Mode: Virtual (via
  Zoom)\n  *   Audience: Open to all interested (Slides and recordings will
  also be shared post-session)\n  *   Topics: Added in confluence<https://a
 pexclearing.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/ADC/pages/8250622042/Lunch+Learn+Ser
 ies+Topic+Roster>\n\n\n\nWe look forward to your participation. Let’s al
 ign our expertise and drive innovation together! Please feel free to forwa
 rd a needed!\n\n\n\n**This is not targeted for an office or a time or spec
 ific audience. We don't expect everyone to join live also. Goal is to reco
 rd and post the slides + video on confluence so that it will become an inv
 entory and can be accessed by anyone any time\n\n\nVineeth Ayyat Kochaniya
 n\n\nSr Director\, Product Management\n\nvayyatkochaniyan@apexfintexhsolut
 ions.com<mailto:vayyatkochaniyan@apexfintexhsolutions.com>\n\n\n\n[Image]\
 n\n\nVineeth Ayyat Kochaniyan is inviting you to a scheduled Zoom meeting.
 \n\nJoin Zoom Meeting - - Please note hosts must use Zoom app or link to s
 tart this meeting.\nhttps://apexclearing.zoom.us/j/99763428337?from=addon\
 n\nOne tap mobile\n+12532158782\,\,99763428337# US (Tacoma)\n+12532050468\
 ,\,99763428337# US\n\nDial by your location\n+1 253 215 8782 US (Tacoma)\n
 +1 253 205 0468 US\n+1 719 359 4580 US\n+1 346 248 7799 US (Houston)\n+1 6
 69 444 9171 US\n+1 669 900 6833 US (San Jose)\n+1 689 278 1000 US\n+1 301 
 715 8592 US (Washington DC)\n+1 305 224 1968 US\n+1 309 205 3325 US\n+1 31
 2 626 6799 US (Chicago)\n+1 360 209 5623 US\n+1 386 347 5053 US\n+1 507 47
 3 4847 US\n+1 564 217 2000 US\n+1 646 876 9923 US (New York)\n+1 646 931 3
 860 US\nMeeting ID: 997 6342 8337\nFind your local number: https://apexcle
 aring.zoom.us/u/abLLUWGQLT\n\nJoin by SIP\n99763428337@zoomcrc.com\n\nJoin
  by H.323\n144.195.19.161 (US West)\n206.247.11.121 (US East)\n115.114.131
 .7 (India Mumbai)\n115.114.115.7 (India Hyderabad)\n159.124.15.191 (Amster
 dam Netherlands)\n159.124.47.249 (Germany)\n159.124.104.213 (Australia Syd
 ney)\n159.124.74.212 (Australia Melbourne)\n170.114.180.219 (Singapore)\n6
